-- Egypt, Arab Fund Sign Loan Deal to Finance New Power Plant, Alam Reports
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2010-12-30T07:08:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/egypt-arab-fund-sign-loan-deal-to-finance-new-power-plant-alam-reports.html
Egypt and the Arab Fund for Economic
and Social Development signed an agreement for a 50 million-
Kuwaiti-dinar ($177.5 million) facility to help finance a power
plant,  Al Alam Al Youm  reported today, citing Electricity
Minister  Hassan Younes .  The total cost of the 750 megawatt station in the city of
Banha is around 4.5 billion Egyptian pounds ($775 million),
according to the Cairo-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ola Galal  at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net . 